Class AnnotationDefinitionTable

java.lang.Object

All Implemented Interfaces:

public class AnnotationDefinitionTable
extends ExternalType

AnnotationDefinitionTable holds the document annotation definitions. This class manages the annotation definitions through the addAnnotationDefinition(TableAnnotationDefinition, int) operation.

Version:
1.3 Derives from ExternalType
Author:
Anthony Bargnesi <abargnesi@selventa.com>

public int addAnnotationDefinition(AnnotationDefinitionTable.TableAnnotationDefinition annotationDefinition,

Adds an annotation definition to the annotationDefinitions set. The insertion index is captured by definitionIndex.

Parameters:

Returns:
int, the index of the added annotation definition, which must be >= 0.

_from

protected void _from(ObjectInput in,
                     ReadCache cache)
              throws IOException,
                     ClassNotFoundException
Reads itself from the input. The supplied cache is an ancillary structure allowing the implementing type to reference a cached copy of an object by its hash value.

The use of the cache is not required. However the use or disuse of the cache should be symmetric according to both ExternalType._from(ObjectInput, ReadCache) and ExternalType._to(ObjectOutput, WriteCache). Put differently, the cache use should be identical in both methods.
